OL,3,CFootball managers shine a light on
OL,4,Csuicide prevention
OL,6,FFormer Liverpool manager Jurgen Klopp
OL,7,Fsaid: "Preventing suicide is an
OL,8,Fimportant issue and tragically too
OL,9,Fmany lives are lost each year. For
OL,10,Fthese reasons, talking openly about
OL,11,Fsuicide is more open than ever."
OL,13,FThe 30-minute Zero Suicide Alliance
OL,14,Ftraining is free for everyone and aims
OL,15,Fto teach skills to have potentially
OL,16,Flife-saving conversations.
OL,18,FOne in four people think of suicide
OL,19,Fduring their lifetime.
